description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialised Women’s Health Physiotherapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Croydon Health Services NHS Trust strives to be at the forefront of responsive and dynamic service provision for patients, which has a vision for providing patient centred care and effective health care for all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Orchid Suite is a nurse led service run by specialist nurses who see patients with bladder, bowel and pelvic floor dysfunction. These patients are assessed by the appropriate nurse specialist, procedures carried out and a treatment plan instigated. We work closely with a multidisciplinary team and receive referrals into the service from many different specialities including Urogynaecology, Urology, Colorectal, Gastroenterology and Neurology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting new post for a dynamic and motivated Women’s Health Physiotherapist to join our team and further enhance the service we provide for these patient. We are looking for a clinician with extensive experience at a highly specialist level in the Women’s Health environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of this role is to undertake a holistic approach to the assessment, diagnosis and management of patients referred. Providing a high quality service that meets the needs of individuals presenting with bladder, bowel and pelvic floor dysfunction using current evidence and education to manage these patients in an efficient effective and supportive way. Working closely with other health care professionals from the primary and secondary care settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our department offers a friendly and supportive working environment which actively supports continuing Professional Development, through an established appraisal system, in-service training and post graduate library facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll need to be :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;HCPC Registered&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Equivalent to Band 6/7 Women’s Health Physio experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Substantial Physiotherapy experience, ideally working in Women’s Health&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Skilled in assessment and treatment of out-patient Obstetric MSK and Continence, Urogynae, Pelvic pain and Sexual Dysfunction patients&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fully competent in Vaginal and Ano-rectal examinations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ideally we would like you to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post Graduate qualification in Women’s Health Physiotherapy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;POGP membership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Acupuncture qualification&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pilates qualification&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with Real-time Ultrasound&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview: 2nd December 2020 (tbc)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
